 Artificial Intelligence Policy research intern 
 Job Description 
Intel's public policy team is one of the most influential ICT policy group in the industry. The team covers broad ICT policies and topics which are communication, cybersecurity, content protection, environment and trade policies. Artificial Intelligence (AI) is getting a fundamental technology of our daily life but still a lot of new technology and use cases are expected to come. One of the challenges for the society is protecting and respecting data and privacy to best utilize the value of date for the society. The team is seeking a graduate intern to support the AI policy research project with the global team. 
The research project will include but are not limited to: 
AI related policy and regulation environmental scan 
Engage with internal and external AI policy stakeholders to identify mid-term policy development plan 
Develop a prototype policy tool to help safer data utilization on AI 
The successful candidate should exhibit the following behavioral traits: 
Excellent verbal and written communication skills. 
Passion for developing a policy for a better society. 
Attention to detail. 
Interpersonal skills to build relationships with a diverse range of people in a virtual environment. 
Visionary and innovation-driven. 
Willing to work with diverse people around the world. 
Qualifications 
You must possess the below minimum qualifications to be initially considered for this position. Preferred qualifications are in addition to the minimum requirements and are considered a plus factor in identifying top candidates. Experience listed below would be obtained through a combination of your school work classes research and or relevant previous job and or internship experiences 
 
Minimum Qualifications: 
Must be pursuing a Master's or PhD degree in public policy, law, electrical engineering, computer engineering, computer science, data scienceor other related field. 
This position is not eligible for employment-based visa/immigration sponsorship. 
Preferred qualifications: 
Previous experience with: 
Technology policy 
Technology standards 
AI technology basics (Machine learning, Deep learning, influencing) 
Data protection 
